# Z-Index Layering Scale

Fixed scale — use these layers, never invent new arbitrary values.

| Layer | z-value | Usage |
|-------|---------|-------|
| Content | `z-10` | Elevated page content (sticky headers within a section) |
| Nav | `z-[40]` | AppNav, agency strip (`z-[41]`), mobile bottom nav |
| Overlay | `z-50` | Standard modals, drawers, popovers, confirmation dialogs |
| Stacked | `z-[60]` | Modal-on-modal (e.g. confirm inside a drawer) |
| Lightbox | `z-[100]` | Fullscreen media viewers and their sub-modals |

## Rules

- **Nav must never block overlays.** The nav sits at `z-[40]`; any `z-50` modal naturally covers it.
- **Never use `z-[140]`+** for navigation. That was the old convention and caused every popup to need inflation.
- Pages that wrap `<AppNav variant="transparent">` in an absolute container should use `z-[40]` on that wrapper.
- If a new overlay needs to stack above another overlay, go one tier up (e.g. `z-[60]`), don't jump to `z-[200]`.
